						<summary><p>#51. a) PIM, goddess shrine; b) begins on the northern part of the curved portion (<foreign>kumuda</foreign>) of the base of the western façade of the sanctuary and continues on the central projection; c) personally located and read in situ; d) ARE 1924, no. 396; Tyagarajan (2014: no. 5, 133–134); e) 15th regnal year of Rājakesarivarman Cakkaravattikaḷ Śrī Kolottoṅkacōḻatēvar; f) probably Kulottuṅga I (<foreign>circa</foreign> 1084 A.D.); g) inscription not read with anyone; h) the beginning is missing, confirming that the temple was reconstructed.</p>

